definition: to come as no surprise/as expected
Italy/Italian/abbr. for 意大利[Yi4 da4 li4]
to hit (the mark)/to be hit by/to suffer/to win (a prize, a lottery)

sentences.english: This is to be expected, though.
sentences.chinese: 不过这也是在意料之中。

sentences.english: That the enemies sallied out was to be thought in his mind.
sentences.chinese: 敌人的突然涌现早在他的意料之中。

sentences.english: Most of the findings are predictable, but a few are surprising.
sentences.chinese: 大多数结果都在意料之中，不过也有一些意外。

sentences.english: Equally unsurprisingly, they looked down on the role of worker.
sentences.chinese: 意料之中的是，他们瞧不起工人。

sentences.english: Although he was not suffering from a serious illness, it was not unexpected.
sentences.chinese: 尽管他没犯什么大病，但他的离去也是在意料之中的。

sentences.english: This is normal. This is to be expected.
sentences.chinese: 这很正常，也是意料之中的事。

sentences.english: According to Noy , fear is both natural and expected.
sentences.chinese: 而在诺伊看来，害怕是很自然的，也是意料之中的。

sentences.english: It should not come as a surprise that the economies of China and Germany have been thriving.
sentences.chinese: 故此，中德两国经济的兴旺完全可在意料之中。

definition: due to/to stem from/to go beyond (also fig. beyond reason, expectations etc)/to go against (expectations)
turned out other than expected (idiom); unexpected
not expected at the outset (idiom)/unforeseen/to be surprised by the turn of events
to be a cinch/in the bag/(of a person) confident of success
that clinches it/that's final/no two ways about it
